# grapher_intersect_mixed_smoke.numos — Phase 10G. Cross-kind intersection
# markers.
#
# Commits "y=x" (an explicit line) and "x^2+y^2=9" (an implicit circle), enters
# Trace and steps once. Proves Phase 10G's cross-kind intersection finder: the
# legacy POI pass only crossed y=f(x) against y=f(x) (it sampled evalAt, which is
# NAN for an implicit slot), so a line meeting a circle showed NO purple marker.
# The unified residual (residualAt: y-f(x) for explicit, evalImplicit for implicit
# / x=f(y)) plus a grid-seeded 2-D Newton (find2DIntersections / newton2D) now
# seeds a purple Intersection marker at BOTH crossings (~±2.12, ±2.12).
#
# The async POI timer paints the markers on completion (poiAsyncTimerCb replots
# when done) since GrapherApp has no per-frame update().
#
# Warning-only: screenshot, NO golden, NOT CI-gated (absent from the
# generate-emulator-candidates CANDIDATES list and every emulator-build.yml step).
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/grapher_intersect_mixed_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 1100 --screenshot out/grapher_intersect_mixed_smoke.ppm --quiet
log "grapher_intersect_mixed: start"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
# Slot 0: y=x (explicit line). down -> Add row; enter -> edit; type; enter commits.
key down
key enter
key y
key =
key x
key enter
wait 30
# Slot 1: x^2+y^2=9 (implicit circle).
key down
key enter
key x
key ^
key 2
key right
key +
key y
key ^
key 2
key right
key =
key 9
key enter
wait 40
# The line auto-traces on Graph entry; one RIGHT step recomputes POIs (the cross-
# kind finder runs in the async POI pass) and the markers paint on completion.
key graph
wait 80
key right
wait 220
screenshot out/grapher_intersect_mixed_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_intersect_mixed: two purple line-circle intersection markers"
